a lid and cook <b>10-12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until fish is cooked to your liking. Set Varoma aside. Carefully remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer fish into a thermal serving bowl or large bowl. Cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Place Varoma back into position, secure Varoma lid and continue to cook vegetables and prawns for a further <b>5-7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until vegetables are cooked to your liking. Transfer vegetables, prawns, sauce and reserved spinach into thermal serving bowl with fish, sprinkle with salt (see Tips) and stir to combine. Garnish with coriander and serve with cooked rice."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace liquid vegetable stock with Vegetable stock paste and water in this recipe. Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe. In step 4 replace liquid stock with 2 teaspoons Vegetable stock paste and 200 g water.","<strong>Baby's serve<\/strong>: omit salt and blend curry (with some cooked rice, if liked) to desired consistency. For an older baby, keep the blended consistency more textured or simply serve as is, cut up as needed.","<strong>Toddler's serve<\/strong>: omit or reduce salt and serve as is, cut up as needed."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","6 portions"]}